a Gilmore|first3=Bryant|last3=Simon|publisher=[[Princeton University Press]]|location=Princeton, NJ|year=2000|isbn=978-0-691-00193-7|url=https://books.google.com/?id=yFvjsEYP7hAC&pg=PA90|ref=harv}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Davis|first=David Brion|authorlink=David Brion Davis|title=Inhuman Bondage: The Rise and Fall of Slavery in the New World|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|location=New York|year=2006|isbn=978-0-19-514073-6|ref=harv|title-link=Inhuman Bondage: The Rise and Fall of Slavery in the New World}}\n* {{Cite book|title=The Encyclopedia of Virginia|isbn=978-0-403-09753-1|publisher=Somerset Publishers|year=1999|location=St. Clair Shores, MI|volume=1|edition=4|ref=CITEREFThe Encyclopedia of Virginia1999}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Feuer|first=A.B.|title= The U.S. Navy in World War I: combat at sea and in the air|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|year=1999|isbn=978-0-275-96212-8|location=Westport, CT|ref=harv}}\n* {{Cite book|title=Bound Away: Virginia and the Westward Movement|first1=David Hackett|last1=Fischer|authorlink1=David Hackett Fischer|first2=James C.|last2=Kelly|publisher=[[University of Virginia Press]]|location=Charlottesville|year=2000|isbn=978-0-8139-1774-0|ref=harv}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Goodwin|first=Bill|url=https://books.google.com/?id=l_JqVwS2krIC|title=Frommer's Virginia|publisher=[[John Wiley & Sons]]|location=Hoboken, NJ|year=2012|edition=11|isbn=978-1-118-22449-6|ref=harv}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Gordon|first=John Steele|url=https://archive.org/details/empireofwealthep0000gord|url-access=registration|page=[https://archive.org/details/empireofwealthep0000gord/page/17 17]|title=An Empire of Wealth: The Epic History of American Economic Power|authorlink=John Steele Gordon|publisher=[[HarperCollins]]|location=New York|year=2004|isbn=978-0-06-009362-4|ref=harv}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=v10uoRwUsuEC|title=A Companion to the Literature and Culture of the American South|first1=Richard J.|last1=Gray|first2=Owen|last2=Robinson|pu