 = https://web.archive.org/web/20100504134533/http://www.nemethistvanpeter.hu/ |archive-date = 2010-05-04 |url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\n==Books, poem booklets==\n* ''Vir\u00e1gnyi vil\u00e1gv\u00e9g'' (versek, Budapest, 1987.)\n* ''A szerepek h\u0171s\u00e9ge'' (irodalmi tanulm\u00e1nyok, Veszpr\u00e9m, 1989.)\n* ''Utak szeptembere'' (versek, Budapest, 1990.)\n* ''Bats\u00e1nyin\u00e9 Baumberg Gabriella versei'' (m\u0171ford\u00edt\u00e1sok, Tapolca, 1992.)\n* ''\u2026a term\u00e9szet \u00f6r\u00f6mk\u00f6nnye'' (balatoni antol\u00f3gia, V\u00f6r\u00f6sber\u00e9ny, 1993.)\n* ''Koncz Istv\u00e1n Magamnak mondom c\u00edm\u0171 v\u00e1logatott versesk\u00f6tete'' (szerkesztette s gondozta - Tapolca, 1995.)\n* ''Orig\u00f3sdi'' (mes\u00e9k - Kamar\u00e1s Istv\u00e1nnal k\u00f6z\u00f6sen - Tapolca, 1996.)\n* ''Angyalvih\u00e1nc Manoph\u00fcl\u00e9ben'' (gyermekversek, Tapolca, 1996.)\n* ''\u00c9gi tetsz\u00e9sre - idelenn'' (a Balaton Akad\u00e9mia k\u00f6nyvsorozat\u00e1nak repert\u00f3riuma, V\u00f6r\u00f6sber\u00e9ny, 1996.)\n* ''Heine-dalosk\u00f6nyv'' (Tapolca, 1997.)\n* ''A bogl\u00e1ri parton Adal\u00e9kok Balatonbogl\u00e1r irodalom \u00e9s m\u0171vel\u0151d\u00e9st\u00f6rt\u00e9net\u00e9hez. Balaton Akad\u00e9mia k\u00f6nyvek'' (szerkesztette - 1998.)\n* ''Bor\u00e1ggal \u00e1ldlak - magyar bordalosk\u00f6nyv - Balaton Akad\u00e9mia k\u00f6nyvek'' (szerkesztette - 1999.)\n* ''Pann\u00f3nia dics\u00e9rete - el\u0151ad\u00e1sok a II. magyar \u00edr\u00f3k, m\u0171ford\u00edt\u00f3k vil\u00e1gtal\u00e1lkoz\u00f3j\u00e1n Balaton Akad\u00e9mia k\u00f6nyvek'' (szerkesztette - 1999.)\n* ''Kamar\u00e1s Istv\u00e1n: Vil\u00e1gverseny a berekben N\u00e9meth Istv\u00e1n P\u00e9ter verseivel'' (Cicero K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, 1999.)\n* ''Herbert Zinkl: Es\u0151\u00e9nek'' (m\u0171ford\u00edt\u00e1sok, Balatonf\u00fcred, 1999.)\n* ''Koldus \u00e9s kir\u00e1lyfi'' (meseopera-librett\u00f3, Balatonf\u00fcred, 2000.)\n* ''100 vers'' (versek, Tapolca, 2000.)\n* ''Kihullt lapok egy napl\u00f3b\u00f3l'' (napl\u00f3k, f\u00f6ljegyz\u00e9sek, Bal\u00e1ca K\u00f6nyvek, Veszpr\u00e9m, 2000.)\n* ''Rilke-k\u00e9pesk\u00f6nyv''  (m\u0171ford\u00edt\u00e1sok, Balatonf\u00fcred, 2000.)\n* ''Gy\u00f6ngyt\u00e1r \u00e9s teklat\u00e9ka'' (versek, Tapolca, 2001.)\n* ''Egry ragyog\u00e1sa'' (versantol\u00f3gia a magyar k\u00f6lt\u0151k Egry J\u00f3zsefhez \u00edrott verseib\u0151l, Balaton\u0151sz\u00f6d, 2001.)\n* ''Kar\u00e1csonyi irka'' (versek \u00e9s m\u0171ford\u00edt\u00e1sok, Z\u00e1nka, 2001.)\n* ''Janus-irka Janus Pannonius 50 epigramm\u00e1ja NIP m\u0171ford\u00edt\u00e1s\u00e1ban/\u00e1tk\u00f6lt\u00e9s\u00e9ben''\n\n==DVDs==\n* ''\u00d6leljen F\u00f6ld, v\u00edz s \u00e9g!'' (balatoni irka Nagy G\u00e1sp\u00e1r eml\u00e9k\u00e9nek, 2007.)\n* ''Megtal\u00e1ljon a Kar\u00e1csony!'' (kar\u00e1csonyi versek orgon\u00e1s zenei al\u00e1fest\u00e9ssel, 2007.)\n* ''H\u00fasv\u00e9ti orat\u00f3rium'' (h\u00fasv\u00e9ti verses DVD, 2008.)\n* ''Angyalvih\u00e1nc Manoph\u00fcl\u00e9ben'' (gyermekversek, 2008.)\n\n==Recognition==\n* Egry J\u00f3zsef orsz\u00e1gos p\u00e1ly\u00e1zat, II. hely - Badacsony, 1976.\n* Egry J\u00f3zsef orsz\u00e1gos p\u00e1ly\u00e1zat, I.hely - Badacsony, 1977.\n* Baraxa-So\u00f3s Alap\u00edtv\u00e1ny d\u00edja, 1985.\n* FMK orsz\u00e1gos vers\u00edr\u00f3 p\u00e1ly\u00e1zat, Bp., I. hely\n* B.A.Z. megye jubileumi irodalmi p\u00e1ly\u00e1zat, Miskolc, 1987., III. hely\n* IRAT irodalmi n\u00edv\u00f3d\u00edj els\u0151 verses k\u00f6tet\u00e9\u00e9rt, Bp., 1989.\n* Pedag\u00f3gusk\u00e9nt v\u00e9gzett \u00f6nk\u00e9pz\u00e9s\u00e9\u00e9rt Fonay-d\u00edj, Veszpr\u00e9m, 1990.\n* Az \u00c9let \u00e9s Irodalom bordalversenye, III. d\u00edj, Budapest, 1992.\n* Salvatore Quasimodo k\u00f6lt\u0151i verseny, k\u00fcl\u00f6nd\u00edj, Balatonf\u00fcred, 1994.\n* Salvatore Quasimodo k\u00f6lt\u0151i versenyben a legjobb 12 k\u00f6z\u00f6tt, 1998.\n* Orsz\u00e1gos Illy\u00e9s Gyula-p\u00e1ly\u00e1zat a k\u00f6lt\u0151 100. sz\u00fclet\u00e9snapj\u00e1n. Magyar Kult\u00fara H\u00e1za, Bp., Corvin t\u00e9r. Tanulm\u00e1nya a legjobb 10 k\u00f6z\u00f6tt, a M\u00f3ricz Zsigmond T\u00e1rsas\u00e1g k\u00fcl\u00f6nd\u00edja, 2002.\n* A \"Tapolca v\u00e1ros\u00e9rt\" kit\u00fcntetettje, 2001.\n\n==Notable citations==\n* Lurk\u00f3s l\u00edra, mack\u00f3s po\u00e9zis<ref>{{cite news |title=Lurk\u00f3s l\u00edra, mack\u00f3s po\u00e9zis |author=Toldi \u00c9va |newspaper=Napl\u00f3 |date=8 March 1991 |url=http://www.nemethistvanpeter.hu/vers/fogadtat.htm |access-date=13 August 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100616044258/http://www.nemethistvanpeter.hu/vers/fogadtat.htm |archive-date=16 June 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* N\u00e9meth Istv\u00e1n P\u00e9ter - K\u00f6lt\u00e9szet napi K\u00f6nyvszemle<ref>{{cite news |title=N\u00e9meth Istv\u00e1n P\u00e9ter - K\u00f6lt\u00e9szet napi K\u00f6nyvszemle |author=Tarj\u00e1n Tam\u00e1s |newspaper=N\u00e9pszabads\u00e1g |year=1988 |url=http://www.nemethistvanpeter.hu/vers/fogadt02.htm |access-date=2010-08-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100616044111/http://www.nemethistvanpeter.hu/vers/fogadt02.htm |archive-date=2010-06-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Gy\u00f6ngyt\u00e1r \u00e9s teklat\u00e9ka<ref>{{cite news |title=N\u00e9meth Istv\u00e1n P\u00e9ter: Gy\u00f6ngyt\u00e1r \u00e9s teklat\u00e9ka |author=Ker\u00e9k Imre |year=2001 |url=http://www.nemethistvanpeter.hu/vers/fogadt03.htm |access-date=2010-08-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100616044252/http://www.nemethistvanpeter.hu/vers/fogadt03.htm |archive-date=2010-06-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Gondolatok N\u00e9meth Istv\u00e1n P\u00e9ter Mit hozt\u00e1l \u2013 T\u0171n\u0151d\u00e9sek a t\u00e1jhaz\u00e1r\u00f3l c\u00edm\u0171 k\u00f6nyv\u00e9nek olvas\u00e1sa k\u00f6zben<ref>{{cite book | title = Gondolatok N\u00e9meth Istv\u00e1n P\u00e9ter Mit hozt\u00e1l \u2013 T\u0171n\u0151d\u00e9sek a t\u00e1jhaz\u00e1r\u00f3l c\u00edm\u0171 k\u00f6nyv\u00e9nek olvas\u00e1sa k\u00f6zben | author = Dr. Szab\u00f3 T. Attila | publisher = \u00daj Horizont Kiad\u00f3 | year = 2003 }}</ref>\n* Rem\u00e9ny, k\u00e9z\u00edr\u00e1sban<ref>{{cite news | title = Rem\u00e9ny, k\u00e9z\u00edr\u00e1sban | author = Toldi \u00c9va | newspaper = Veszpr\u00e9m Megyei Napl\u00f3 | date = 13 February 2009 | url = http://www.nemethistvanpeter.hu/vers/naplo0902.htm | page = 7 | access-date = 13 August 2010 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100616044348/http://www.nemethistvanpeter.hu/vers/naplo0902.htm | archive-date = 16 June 2010 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\nBeyond journal articles on the works of N\u00e9meth, several citations appear also on the internet, e.g. Ar\u00e1csi anakreon,<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.napkut.hu/naput_2006/2006_10/kava_teka_10.htm |title = Ar\u00e1csi anakreon (interj\u00fa) }}</ref> Balatoni haikuk,<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.terebess.hu/haiku/nemethi.html |title = Balatoni haikuk (Terebess) }}</ref> or A m\u0171ford\u00edt\u00e1s f\u00e9ny\u0171z\u00e9se\n.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.epa.oszk.hu/00000/00016/00029/970912.htm |title = A m\u0171ford\u00edt\u00e1s f\u00e9ny\u0171z\u00e9se (cikk) }}</ref>\n\n==Media appearances==\n* {{cite news |title= Visszah\u00faz\u00f3dni j\u00f6tt ide. Rubin Szil\u00e1rd \u00edr\u00f3 a tapolcai k\u00f6lt\u0151 szem\u00e9vel. |author=Szij\u00e1rt\u00f3 J |newspaper=Veszpr\u00e9m Megyei NAPL\u00d3 |date=22 April 2010 }}\n* {{cite news |title= Hazal\u00e1togatott H\u00e1romf\u00e1ra Ker\u00e9k Imre k\u00f6lt\u0151. |author=Meiszterics E |newspaper=Somogyi H\u00edrlap |date=18 May 2010 }}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Hungarian literature}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nemeth, Istvan Peter}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Hungarian poets]]\n[[Category:Hungarian male poets]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian poets]]\n[[Category:20th-century Hungarian male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male writers]]\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:recat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Istv%C3%A1n_P%C3%A9ter_N%C3%A9meth"}
{"title_page": "Endre Kukorelly", "text_new": "{{Expand Hungarian|B\u00e9kesi L\u00e1szl\u00f3|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox officeholder \n| name           = Endre Kukorelly\n| image          =Irolap kukorelly portrait.jpg\n| imagesize      =\n| order          = [[National Assembly of Hungary|Member of the National Assembly]]\n| term_start     = 14 May 2010\n| term_end       = 23 September 2012\n| president      =\n| predecessor    =\n| successor      =\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1951|4|26|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Budapest]], [[People's Republic of Hungary|Hungary]]\n| profession     = writer, poet\n| party          = [[Politics Can Be Different|LMP]]\n| otherparty     =\n|}}\n{{eastern name order|Kukorelly Endre}}\n'''Endre Kukorelly''' (born April 26, 1951)<ref name=\"Biography\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parlament.hu/kepv/eletrajz/hu/k114.htm |archive-url=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20111221114935/http://www.parlament.hu/kepv/eletrajz/hu/k114.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date=2011-12-21 |title=''Biography'' |publisher=[[National Assembly of Hungary|Orsz\u00e1ggy\u0171l\u00e9s]] }}</ref> is a Hungarian writer, poet and journalist. He is a teacher of the [[Hungarian University of Fine Arts]]. He was also an editor of the ''[[Magyar Narancs]]''.\n\n==Political career==\nKukorelly is a founding member of the [[Politics Can Be Different]] (LMP). He ran for an individual seat in [[Szentendre]], [[Pest County]] Constituency XI during the [[2010 Hungarian parliamentary election|2010 parliamentary election]]. He became a [[National Assembly of Hungary|member of the National Assembly]] (MP) from the first place of LMP's Pest County Regional List on May 14, 2010.<ref name=\"Register\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parlament.hu/internet/plsql/ogy_kpv.kepv_adat?p_azon=k114&p_ckl=39|title=''Register'' |publisher=[[National Assembly of Hungary|Orsz\u00e1ggy\u0171l\u00e9s]]}}</ref> He worked in the Committee on Sports and Tourism. He resigned from his mandate due to lack of confidence on September 23, 2012. He was replaced by [[Szilvia Lengyel]] on October 8, 2012.<ref>[http://www.nepszava.hu/articles/article.php?id=587158&referer_id=friss Kukorelly Endre lemondott parlamenti mand\u00e1tum\u00e1r\u00f3l]</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* ''A val\u00f3s\u00e1g \u00e9dess\u00e9ge'' (poems, 1984, Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest)\n* ''Mani\u00e8re'' (poems, 1986, Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest)\n* ''\u00c9n senkivel sem \u00fcld\u00f6g\u00e9lek'' (poems, 1989, Pannon K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest)\n* ''A Mem\u00f3ria-part'' (novel, 1990, Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest, Book Of The Year Award; translated into five languages between 1996 and 2000)\n* ''Azt mondja aki \u00e9l'' (prose poems, 1991, Jelenkor Irodalmi \u00e9s M\u0171v\u00e9szeti Kiad\u00f3, [[P\u00e9cs]])\n* ''Egy gy\u00f3gyn\u00f6v\u00e9ny-kert'' (selected poems, 1993, Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest; translated into [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] in 1997)\n* ''Napos ter\u00fclet'' (prose poems, 1994)\n* ''Budapest \u2013 Pap\u00edrv\u00e1ros'' (photo gallery book, 1994, with photos of K\u00e1roly Gink)\n* ''Mintha m\u00e1r t\u00fal sok\u00e1ig \u00e1llna'' (poems, 1995, Budapest)\n* ''Kedvenxc'' (essays, 1996; translated into [[German language|German]] in 1999)\n* ''H.\u00d6.L.D.E.R.L.I.N.'' (poem cycle, 1999)\n* ''H\u00e1rom 100 darab'' (novelette, Jelenkor Irodalmi \u00e9s M\u0171v\u00e9szeti kiad\u00f3, P\u00e9cs, 1999)\n* ''Rom: A Szovjet\u00f3ni\u00f3 t\u00f6rt\u00e9nete'' (novel, 2000)\n* ''Kicsit majd kevesebbet j\u00e1rk\u00e1lok'' (writings, 2001)\n* ''T\u00fcnd\u00e9rV\u00f6lgy, avagy Az emberi sz\u00edv rejtelmeir\u0151l'' (novel, 2003, harmadik kiad\u00e1s 2007)\n* ''Samunadr\u00e1g'' (poems for children, 2005, Kalligram K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest)\n* ''Rom. A komonizmus t\u00f6rt\u00e9nete'' (novel, 2006, enlarged edition)\n* ''Ezer \u00e9s 3 avagy A n\u0151kben rejl\u0151 sz\u00edv '' (novel, 2009, Kalligram K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest)\n* ''Mennyit hib\u00e1zok, te \u00faristen'' (Kalligram K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, 2010)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Endre Kukorelly}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.pimmedia.hu/object.7B2531AE-D436-4449-BABA-E0AFB6D1EF17.ivy |publisher=Pet\u0151fi Irodalmi M\u00fazeum (PIM M\u00e9dia)|title=Kukorelly Endre|language=Hungarian|accessdate=2009-11-16}}\n* {{cite book|url=http://mek.oszk.hu/01300/01375/01375.htm|author=Zsolt Farkas|title=Kukorelly Endre|language=Hungarian|publisher=Kalligram|location=Bratislava|year=1996|isbn=80-7149-152-7}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.hunlit.hu/kukorellyendre |publisher=A Magyar K\u00f6nyv Alap\u00edtv\u00e1ny adatb\u00e1zisa|title=Kukorelly Endre|language=Hungarian|accessdate=2009-11-16}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.kontextus.hu/kia/kia.php?ID=77&action=full|publisher=Kort\u00e1rs Irodalmi Adatt\u00e1r|title=Kukorelly Endre|language=Hungarian|accessdate=2009-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100718230805/http://www.kontextus.hu/kia/kia.php?ID=77&action=full|archive-date=2010-07-18|url-status=dead}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.netlexikon.hu/yrk/hfreqrsvarq/1189 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130107195326/http://www.netlexikon.hu/yrk/hfreqrsvarq/1189 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-01-07 |publisher=Netlexikon.hu |language=Hungarian |accessdate=2009-11-16 |title=Kukorelly Endre }}\n* {{cite web |url=http://kukorelly.irolap.hu/hu/node/1283 |title=\u00c9letrajz |publisher=Kukorelly.irolap.hu |language=Hungarian |accessdate=2009-11-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090609050614/http://kukorelly.irolap.hu/hu/node/1283 |archivedate=2009-06-09 }}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.hu/videotar/?id=31897|title=Kukorelly a Z\u00e1r\u00f3r\u00e1ban|date=2008-10-23|language=Hungarian|accessdate=2009-11-16|publisher=mtv.hu}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://my.dunatv.hu/musor/videotar?vid=660460|title=Azt mondja, aki \u00e9l. Vers Karalyos G\u00e1bor el\u0151ad\u00e1s\u00e1ban|publisher=dunatv.hu|language=Hungarian|accessdate=2012-07-22}}\n\n{{Hungarian literature}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kukorelly, Endre}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male poets]]\n[[Category:Hungarian journalists]]\n[[Category:Hungarian literary critics]]\n[[Category:Hungarian academics]]\n[[Category:Politics Can Be Different politicians]]\n[[Category:Members of the National Assembly of Hungary (2010\u20132014)]]\n[[Category:Writers from Budapest]]\n[[Category:Hungarian University of Fine Arts faculty]]\n[[Category:20th-century Hungarian poets]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian poets]]\n[[Category:20th-century Hungarian male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian male writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Expand Hungarian|B\u00e9kesi L\u00e1szl\u00f3|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox officeholder \n| name           = Endre Kukorelly\n| image          =Irolap kukorelly portrait.jpg\n| imagesize      =\n| order          = [[National Assembly of Hungary|Member of the National Assembly]]\n| term_start     = 14 May 2010\n| term_end       = 23 September 2012\n| president      =\n| predecessor    =\n| successor      =\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1951|4|26|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Budapest]], [[People's Republic of Hungary|Hungary]]\n| profession     = writer, poet\n| party          = [[Politics Can Be Different|LMP]]\n| otherparty     =\n|}}\n{{eastern name order|Kukorelly Endre}}\n'''Endre Kukorelly''' (born April 26, 1951)<ref name=\"Biography\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parlament.hu/kepv/eletrajz/hu/k114.htm |archive-url=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20111221114935/http://www.parlament.hu/kepv/eletrajz/hu/k114.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date=2011-12-21 |title=''Biography'' |publisher=[[National Assembly of Hungary|Orsz\u00e1ggy\u0171l\u00e9s]] }}</ref> is a Hungarian writer, poet and journalist. He is a teacher of the [[Hungarian University of Fine Arts]]. He was also an editor of the ''[[Magyar Narancs]]''.\n\n==Political career==\nKukorelly is a founding member of the [[Politics Can Be Different]] (LMP). He ran for an individual seat in [[Szentendre]], [[Pest County]] Constituency XI during the [[2010 Hungarian parliamentary election|2010 parliamentary election]]. He became a [[National Assembly of Hungary|member of the National Assembly]] (MP) from the first place of LMP's Pest County Regional List on May 14, 2010.<ref name=\"Register\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parlament.hu/internet/plsql/ogy_kpv.kepv_adat?p_azon=k114&p_ckl=39|title=''Register'' |publisher=[[National Assembly of Hungary|Orsz\u00e1ggy\u0171l\u00e9s]]}}</ref> He worked in the Committee on Sports and Tourism. He resigned from his mandate due to lack of confidence on September 23, 2012. He was replaced by [[Szilvia Lengyel]] on October 8, 2012.<ref>[http://www.nepszava.hu/articles/article.php?id=587158&referer_id=friss Kukorelly Endre lemondott parlamenti mand\u00e1tum\u00e1r\u00f3l]</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* ''A val\u00f3s\u00e1g \u00e9dess\u00e9ge'' (poems, 1984, Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest)\n* ''Mani\u00e8re'' (poems, 1986, Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest)\n* ''\u00c9n senkivel sem \u00fcld\u00f6g\u00e9lek'' (poems, 1989, Pannon K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest)\n* ''A Mem\u00f3ria-part'' (novel, 1990, Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest, Book Of The Year Award; translated into five languages between 1996 and 2000)\n* ''Azt mondja aki \u00e9l'' (prose poems, 1991, Jelenkor Irodalmi \u00e9s M\u0171v\u00e9szeti Kiad\u00f3, [[P\u00e9cs]])\n* ''Egy gy\u00f3gyn\u00f6v\u00e9ny-kert'' (selected poems, 1993, Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest; translated into [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] in 1997)\n* ''Napos ter\u00fclet'' (prose poems, 1994)\n* ''Budapest \u2013 Pap\u00edrv\u00e1ros'' (photo gallery book, 1994, with photos of K\u00e1roly Gink)\n* ''Mintha m\u00e1r t\u00fal sok\u00e1ig \u00e1llna'' (poems, 1995, Budapest)\n* ''Kedvenxc'' (essays, 1996; translated into [[German language|German]] in 1999)\n* ''H.\u00d6.L.D.E.R.L.I.N.'' (poem cycle, 1999)\n* ''H\u00e1rom 100 darab'' (novelette, Jelenkor Irodalmi \u00e9s M\u0171v\u00e9szeti kiad\u00f3, P\u00e9cs, 1999)\n* ''Rom: A Szovjet\u00f3ni\u00f3 t\u00f6rt\u00e9nete'' (novel, 2000)\n* ''Kicsit majd kevesebbet j\u00e1rk\u00e1lok'' (writings, 2001)\n* ''T\u00fcnd\u00e9rV\u00f6lgy, avagy Az emberi sz\u00edv rejtelmeir\u0151l'' (novel, 2003, harmadik kiad\u00e1s 2007)\n* ''Samunadr\u00e1g'' (poems for children, 2005, Kalligram K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest)\n* ''Rom. A komonizmus t\u00f6rt\u00e9nete'' (novel, 2006, enlarged edition)\n* ''Ezer \u00e9s 3 avagy A n\u0151kben rejl\u0151 sz\u00edv '' (novel, 2009, Kalligram K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, Budapest)\n* ''Mennyit hib\u00e1zok, te \u00faristen'' (Kalligram K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3, 2010)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Endre Kukorelly}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.pimmedia.hu/object.7B2531AE-D436-4449-BABA-E0AFB6D1EF17.ivy |publisher=Pet\u0151fi Irodalmi M\u00fazeum (PIM M\u00e9dia)|title=Kukorelly Endre|language=Hungarian|accessdate=2009-11-16}}\n* {{cite book|url=http://mek.oszk.hu/01300/01375/01375.htm|author=Zsolt Farkas|title=Kukorelly Endre|language=Hungarian|publisher=Kalligram|location=Bratislava|year=1996|isbn=80-7149-152-7}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.hunlit.hu/kukorellyendre |publisher=A Magyar K\u00f6nyv Alap\u00edtv\u00e1ny adatb\u00e1zisa|title=Kukorelly Endre|language=Hungarian|accessdate=2009-11-16}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.kontextus.hu/kia/kia.php?ID=77&action=full|publisher=Kort\u00e1rs Irodalmi Adatt\u00e1r|title=Kukorelly Endre|language=Hungarian|accessdate=2009-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100718230805/http://www.kontextus.hu/kia/kia.php?ID=77&action=full|archive-date=2010-07-18|url-status=dead}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.netlexikon.hu/yrk/hfreqrsvarq/1189 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130107195326/http://www.netlexikon.hu/yrk/hfreqrsvarq/1189 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-01-07 |publisher=Netlexikon.hu |language=Hungarian |accessdate=2009-11-16 |title=Kukorelly Endre }}\n* {{cite web |url=http://kukorelly.irolap.hu/hu/node/1283 |title=\u00c9letrajz |publisher=Kukorelly.irolap.hu |language=Hungarian |accessdate=2009-11-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090609050614/http://kukorelly.irolap.hu/hu/node/1283 |archivedate=2009-06-09 }}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.hu/videotar/?id=31897|title=Kukorelly a Z\u00e1r\u00f3r\u00e1ban|date=2008-10-23|language=Hungarian|accessdate=2009-11-16|publisher=mtv.hu}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://my.dunatv.hu/musor/videotar?vid=660460|title=Azt mondja, aki \u00e9l. Vers Karalyos G\u00e1bor el\u0151ad\u00e1s\u00e1ban|publisher=dunatv.hu|language=Hungarian|accessdate=2012-07-22}}\n\n{{Hungarian literature}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kukorelly, Endre}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male poets]]\n[[Category:Hungarian journalists]]\n[[Category:Hungarian literary critics]]\n[[Category:Hungarian academics]]\n[[Category:Politics Can Be Different politicians]]\n[[Category:Members of the National Assembly of Hungary (2010\u20132014)]]\n[[Category:Writers from Budapest]]\n[[Category:Hungarian University of Fine Arts faculty]]\n[[Category:20th-century Hungarian poets]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian poets]]\n[[Category:20th-century Hungarian male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male writers]]\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:recat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endre_Kukorelly"}
{"title_page": "Canada Soccer Hall of Fame", "text_new": "{{Use Canadian English|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox museum\n|name=            '''Canada Soccer Hall of Fame'''\n|image=\n|established=     1997\n|location=         [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n|type          = Sport museum\n|director      =\n|curator       =\n|visitors      =\n|website     = [https://canadasoccer.com/hall-of-fame-s14653 CanadaSoccer.com]\n}}\n\nThe '''Canada Soccer Hall of Fame''' honours people and institutions for their contributions to [[Soccer in Canada|Canadian soccer]]. It was founded in 1997 by the [[Ontario Soccer Association]] and was originally located in [[Vaughan, Ontario]]. From 2000 to 2018, the Canada Soccer Hall of Fame has inducted 114 players, 13 managers/coaches, 10 officials, and 40 builders as honoured members. Additionally, the Canada Soccer Hall of Fame has recognized 13 teams of distinction and seven organizations of distinction.\n\nAfter the [[Canadian Soccer Association]] Alumni Association was founded in 1987 and then The Soccer Hall of Fame was founded by the [[Ontario Soccer Association]] in 1997 (which was operated in [[Vaughan, Ontario]]), the new Canada Soccer Hall of Fame was launched in May 2017 under the direction of the [[Canadian Soccer Association]] in [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]].<ref>http://www.680news.com/2017/05/15/canada-soccer-hall-of-fame-is-getting-a-rebrand-and-new-management/</ref> All previously-inducted members of The Soccer Hall of Fame as well as a catch-up class of 17 legends were named to the new Canada Soccer Hall of Fame.<ref>https://canadasoccer.com/canada-soccer-hall-of-fame-launches-new-name-logo-and-mission-p160786</ref>\n\n==Honoured members 2000\u20132019==\nFrom 2000 to 2018, the Canada Soccer Hall of Fame has inducted 177 honoured members. The honoured members are organized in four categories: Players, Coaches/Managers, Officials, and Builders. The next class of honoured members will be inducted in 2019.\n\nNames in italics are those persons inducted under the \"Pioneer\" category (established in 2007) or \"Veteran Canadian Players\" category (as the category was renamed in 2017). The next group of Veteran Canadian Players will be inducted in 2019.<ref name=\"Nominations\">{{cite web|url=https://www.canadasoccer.com/nominations-canadian-players-p161325|title=Nominations|website=Google|author1=Canada Soccer|accessdate=September 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Players===\n{|\n|-\n|valign=\"top\"|\n*[[Frank Ambler]]: 2019\n*[[George Anderson (Canadian soccer)|''George Anderson'']]: 2015\n*[[Dick Arends]]: 2000\n*[[Garry Ayre]]: 2005\n*[[Eddie Bak]]: 2019\n*[[Jim Blundell]]: 2019\n*[[Bob Bolitho]]: 2004\n*[[Walter Bowman]]: 2008\n*[[Jack Brand (soccer)|Jack Brand]]: 2008\n*[[Jim Brennan]]: 2015\n*[[Ian Bridge]]: 2003\n*[[Alex Bunbury]]: 2006\n*[[Silvana Burtini]]: 2010\n*[[Buster Cairns]]: 2001\n*[[Geordie Campbell]]: 2000\n*[[Connie Cant]]: 2007\n*''Roland Castonguay'': 2013 \n*''Paul-\u00c9mile Castonguay'': 2013\n*''Marcel Castonguay'': 2013\n*[[John Catliff]]: 2004\n*[[Candace Chapman]]: 2018\n*[[Sam Chedgzoy]]: 2005\n*[[Tony Chursky]]: 2004\n*''Joe Clulow'': 2017\n*[[Carlo Corazzin]]: 2012\n*''Jock Coulter'': 2017\n*[[Jack Cowan]]: 2000\n*[[Errol Crossan]]: 2000\n*[[Nick Dasovic]]: 2011\n*[[Tracy David]]: 2003\n*''Eddie Derby'': 2017\n*[[Jason deVos]]: 2013\n|width=\"33\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n*''Fred Dierden'': 2017\n*[[Paul Dolan (soccer)|Paul Dolan]]: 2004\n*[[Geri Donnelly]]: 2014\n*[[Jimmy Douglas (Canadian soccer)|Jimmy Douglas]]: 2001\n*''Ernie Edmunds'': 2017\n*[[Neil Ellett]]: 2009\n*[[Bill Findler]]: 2007\n*''[[Pete Fitzpatrick|Larry Fitzpatrick]]'': 2017\n*[[Craig Forrest]]: 2007\n*[[Bill Gill (soccer)|Bill Gill]]: 2019\n*''[[George Graham (soccer)|George Graham]]'': 2017\n*[[Gerry Gray]]: 2001\n*[[Doug Greig]]: 2002\n*[[Art Halliwell]]: 2001\n*[[Bob Harley]]: 2003\n*[[Trevor Harvey (footballer)|Trevor Harvey]]: 2004\n*[[Janine Helland]]: 2013\n*[[Randee Hermus]]: 2019\n*[[Charmaine Hooper]]: 2012\n*[[Lyndon Hooper]]: 2011\n*[[Art Hughes (Canadian soccer)|Art Hughes]]: 2001\n*[[Robert Iarusci]]: 2000\n*[[Gordie Ion]]: 2010\n*[[Paul James (soccer)|Paul James]]: 2003\n*[[Glen Johnson (soccer)|Glen Johnson]]: 2007\n*[[Angela Kelly (soccer)|Angela Kelly]]: 2004\n*[[Joe Kennaway]]: 2000\n*[[Victor Kodelja]]: 2011\n*[[Kara Lang]]: 2015\n*''Bobby Lavery'': 2017\n*[[Bob Lenarduzzi]]: 2001\n*[[Sam Lenarduzzi]]: 2000\n|width=\"33\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n*[[Tino Lettieri]]: 2001\n*[[John Limniatis]]: 2009\n*''Eddie MacLaine'': 2017\n*[[Harry Manson (soccer)|''Harry Manson'']]: 2014\n*[[Carmine Marcantonio]]: 2014\n*[[Don Matheson (soccer)|Don Matheson]]: 2019\n*''Bill Matthews'': 2017\n*[[Whitey McDonald|Robert McDonald]]: 2000\n*[[Joan McEachern]]: 2009\n*[[John McGrane]]: 2008\n*[[Kevin McKenna]]: 2019\n*[[Norman McLeod (soccer)|Normie McLeod]]: 2005\n*[[Wes McLeod]]: 2005\n*[[Doug McMahon]]: 2002\n*[[Colin Miller (soccer)|Colin Miller]]: 2005\n*[[Dale Mitchell (soccer)|Dale Mitchell]]: 2002\n*[[Domenic Mobilio]]: 2007\n*''Jimmy Moir'': 2017\n*[[Terry Moore (soccer)|Terry Moore]]: 2005\n*[[Isabelle Morneau]]: 2014\n*[[Andrea Neil]]: 2012\n*''Jimmy Nelson'': 2017\n*[[Bobby Newbold]]: 2019\n*[[Jimmy Nicholl]]: 2011\n*[[Pat Onstad]]: 2015\n*[[Buzz Parsons]]: 2003\n*[[Ken Pears]]: 2000\n*[[Paul Peschisolido]]: 2013\n*[[Brian Philley]]: 2003\n*[[Pat Philley]]: 2004\n*[[Harry Phillips (soccer)|Harry Phillips]]: 2019\n*[[Tomasz Radzinski]]: 2018\n|width=\"33\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n*[[Randy Ragan]]: 2002\n*[[Michelle Ring-Passant]]: 2005\n*[[Brian Robinson (soccer)|Brian Robinson]]: 2006\n*[[Randy Samuel]]: 2006\n*[[John Schepers]]: 2019\n*[[Branko Segota]]: 2002\n*[[Carrie Serwetnyk]]: 2001\n*''Alec Smith'': 2017\n*[[Bobby Smith (Canadian soccer)|Bobby Smith]]: 2019\n*[[Jimmy Spencer (soccer)|Jimmy Spencer]]: 2003\n*''[[Andy Stevens]]'': 2017\n*[[Mike Stojanovic]]: 2009\n*[[Paul Stalteri]]: 2017\n*[[Gary Stevens (soccer)|Gary Stevens]]: 2019\n*[[Gogie S