er executive)|George Anderson]]: 2000\n*''Arther \"Pop\" Arnold'': 2008\n*Brian Avey: 2010\n*Angus Barrett: 2012\n*[[Herb Capozzi]]: 2007\n*Jeff Cross: 2004\n*Sam Davidson: 2000\n*Gus Etchegarry: 2007\n*William Fenton: 2008\n*Jim Fleming: 2007\n|width=\"33\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n*David Forsyth: 2000\n*Tomas Fried: 2000\n*Dave Fryatt: 2000\n*Bill Gilhespy: 2013\n*Rudy Gittens: 2007\n*[[George Gross (journalist)|George Gross]]: 2006\n*William Hoyle: 2011\n*[[Jim Hubay]]: 2015\n*Alex Hylan: 2013\n*Colin Jose: 2009\n|width=\"33\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n*[[John Kerr, Sr.]]: 2015\n*Eric King: 2002\n*[[Graham Leggat]]: 2001\n*John McMahon: 2001\n*[[Luigi Moro]]: 2000\n*Kevin Muldoon: 2013\n*''[[Len Peto]]'': 2011\n*Pat Quinn: 2004\n*''John Richardson'': 2012\n*''Tom Robertson'': 2007\n|width=\"33\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n*''John Russell'': 2010\n*Aubrey Sanford: 2003\n*Georges Schwartz: 2005\n*William Simpson: 2000\n*Alan Southard : 2003\n*[[Frederick Stambrook]]: 2006\n*[[Steve Stavro]]: 2005\n*[[William Stirling (soccer)|William Stirling]]: 2000\n*[[Les Wilson (soccer)|Les Wilson]]: 2008\n*Derek Wisdom: 2009\n|}\n\n==Teams and Clubs of Distinction==\n\n===Teams of Distinction===\n{|\n|-\n|valign=\"top\"|\n* 1888 [[Canada men's national soccer team#Early years|Canadian men's team]]: 2003\n* [[Football at the 1904 Summer Olympics|1904]] [[Galt F.C.|Galt Football Club]]: 2004\n* 1907 [[Calgary Callies|Calgary Caledonians]]: 2007\n* 1924 [[Canada men's national soccer team#Early years|Canadian men's team]]: 2008\n* 1928 [[Westminster Royals]]: 2005\n* 1933 [[Toronto Scottish F.C.|Toronto Scottish]] \u2013 2006\n* [[1976 North American Soccer League season|1976]] [[Toronto Metros-Croatia]]: 2010\n|width=\"33\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n* 1979 [[Vancouver Whitecaps (1974\u201384)|Vancouver Whitecaps]]: 2011\n* 1984 Canadian [[Football at the 1984 Summer Olympics|Olympic]] men's team: 2013\n* 1986 Canadian [[1986 FIFA World Cup squads#.C2.A0Canada|FIFA World Cup]] men's team: 2009\n* 1989 Canadian [[1989 Francophone Games|Francophone Games]] men's team: 2012\n* 1998 Canadian [[1998 CONCACAF Women's Championship|CONCACAF Champion]] women's team: 2015\n* 2000 Canadian [[2000 CONCACAF Gold Cup|Gold Cup Champion]] men's team: 2014\n|}\n\n===Organizations of distinction===\n*Edmonton Angels: 2014\n*Montreal Carsteel: 2015\n*Robbie International Youth Tournament: 2014\n*[[Toronto Ulster United]]: 2011\n*[[Vancouver Columbus F.C.]]: 2013\n*[[Vancouver Firefighters]]: 2010\n*Victoria West: 2012\n\n==Past awards==\n\n===Brian Budd Award recipients===\nThe Brian Budd Award recognizes those who have excelled both in soccer and in another endeavours but who might not otherwise qualify for induction. The candidate must exemplify good character, show outstanding dedication, achievements and leadership in developing soccer in Canada and provide inspiration to past, present and future generations.<ref>http://www.thesoccerhalloffame.ca/brian-budd-award</ref> The award honours the late [[Brian Budd]], a Canadian soccer player who won the [[Superstars]] World Championship competition three years in a row from 1978 to 1980.\n\n*Marc Rizzardo: 2014<ref>http://www.canadasoccer.com/marc-rizzardo-to-receive-2014-brian-budd-award-p156854</ref>\n*[[Soccer Central Matchday|Gerry Dobson]]: 2013\n*Carl Shearer: 2012\n*[[Peter Sloly]]: 2011\n*[[Peter Zezel]]: 2010\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Sports|Canada}}\n* {{Official website|https://canadasoccer.com/hall-of-fame-s14653}}\n* [https://issuu.com/canadasoccer/docs/2017_pdf_cs_hall_of_fame_class Canada Soccer Hall of Fame Class of 2017]\n* [http://www.cbc.ca/sports/soccer/story/2008/11/25/canadian-soccer.html Limniatis to be inducted into Canadian Soccer Hall of Fame]\n\n{{Canadian Soccer Hall of Fame}}\n{{Soccer in Canada}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Canadian Soccer Hall Of Fame}}\n[[Category:Association football museums and halls of fame]]\n[[Category:Halls of fame in Canada]]\n[[Category:Canadian soccer trophies and awards]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Canadian English|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox museum\n|name=            '''Canada Soccer Hall of Fame'''\n|image=\n|established=     1997\n|location=         [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n|type          = Sport museum\n|director      =\n|curator       =\n|visitors      =\n|website     = [https://canadasoccer.com/hall-of-fame-s14653 CanadaSoccer.com]\n}}\n\nThe '''Canada Soccer Hall of Fame''' honours people and institutions for their contributions to [[Soccer in Canada|Canadian soccer]]. It was founded in 1997 by the [[Ontario Soccer Association]] and was originally located in [[Vaughan, Ontario]]. From 2000 to 2018, the Canada Soccer Hall of Fame has inducted 114 players, 13 managers/coaches, 10 officials, and 40 builders as honoured members. Additionally, the Canada Soccer Hall of Fame has recognized 13 teams of distinction and seven organizations of distinction.\n\nAfter the [[Canadian Soccer Association]] Alumni Association was founded in 1987 and then The Soccer Hall of Fame was founded by the [[Ontario Soccer Association]] in 1997 (which was operated in [[Vaughan, Ontario]]), the new Canada Soccer Hall of Fame was launched in May 2017 under the direction of the [[Canadian Soccer Association]] in [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]].<ref>http://www.680news.com/2017/05/15/canada-soccer-hall-of-fame-is-getting-a-rebrand-and-new-management/</ref> All previously-inducted members of The Soccer Hall of Fame as well as a catch-up class of 17 legends were named to the new Canada Soccer Hall of Fame.<ref>https://canadasoccer.com/canada-soccer-hall-of-fame-launches-new-name-logo-and-mission-p160786</ref>\n\n==Honoured members 2000\u20132019==\nFrom 2000 to 2018, the Canada Soccer Hall of Fame has inducted 177 honoured members. The honoured members are organized in four categories: Players, Coaches/Managers, Officials, and Builders. The next class of honoured members will be inducted in 2019.\n\nNames in italics are those persons inducted under the \"Pioneer\" category (established in 2007) or \"Veteran Canadian Players\" category (as the category was renamed in 2017). The next group of Veteran Canadian Players will be inducted in 2019.<ref name=\"Nominations\">{{cite web|url=https://www.canadasoccer.com/nominations-canadian-players-p161325|title=Nominations|website=Google|author1=Canada Soccer|accessdate=September 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Players===\n{|\n|-\n|valign=\"top\"|\n*[[Frank Ambler]]: 2019\n*[[George Anderson (Canadian soccer)|''George Anderson'']]: 2015\n*[[Dick Arends]]: 2000\n*[[Garry Ayre]]: 2005\n*[[Eddie Bak]]: 2019\n*[[Jim Blundell]]: 2019\n*[[Bob Bolitho]]: 2004\n*[[Walter Bowman]]: 2008\n*[[Jack Brand (soccer)|Jack Brand]]: 2008\n*[[Jim Brennan]]: 2015\n*[[Ian Bridge]]: 2003\n*[[Alex Bunbury]]: 2006\n*[[Silvana Burtini]]: 2010\n*[[Buster Cairns]]: 2001\n*[[Geordie Campbell]]: 2000\n*[[Connie Cant]]: 2007\n*''Roland Castonguay'': 2013 \n*''Paul-\u00c9mile Castonguay'': 2013\n*''Marcel Castonguay'': 2013\n*[[John Catliff]]: 2004\n*[[Candace Chapman]]: 2018\n*[[Sam Chedgzoy]]: 2005\n*[[Tony Chursky]]: 2004\n*''Joe Clulow'': 2017\n*[[Carlo Corazzin]]: 2012\n*''Jock Coulter'': 2017\n*[[Jack Cowan]]: 2000\n*[[Errol Crossan]]: 2000\n*[[Nick Dasovic]]: 2011\n*[[Tracy David]]: 2003\n*''Eddie Derby'': 2017\n*[[Jason deVos]]: 2013\n|width=\"33\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n*''Fred Dierden'': 2017\n*[[Paul Dolan (soccer)|Paul Dolan]]: 2004\n*[[Geri Donnelly]]: 2014\n*[[Jimmy Douglas (Canadian soccer)|Jimmy Douglas]]: 2001\n*''Ernie Edmunds'': 2017\n*[[Neil Ellett]]: 2009\n*[[Bill Findler]]: 2007\n*''[[Pete Fitzpatrick|Larry Fitzpatrick]]'': 2017\n*[[Craig Forrest]]: 2007\n*[[Bill Gill (soccer)|Bill Gill]]: 2019\n*''[[George Graham (soccer)|George Graham]]'': 2017\n*[[Gerry Gray]]: 2001\n*[[Doug Greig]]: 2002\n*[[Art Halliwell]]: 2001\n*[[Bob Harley]]: 2003\n*[[Trevor Harvey (footballer)|Trevor Harvey]]: 2004\n*[[Janine Helland]]: 2013\n*[[Randee Hermus]]: 2019\n*[[Charmai